<br>
Buff list:<br>
<br>
Blessing of Aegolism (1150) -or- Ancient: BoA (1300) - but I don't think anyone has this yet<br>
<br>
Divine Str. / Brells Barrier (200)<br>
<br>
Khura's Focus (430)<br>
<br>
*cough* additional HP buff *cough* (380) (not endorsing this - just saying it's possible to do)<br>
<br>
His HP unbuffed should be in the 5700 range - 5808 is the MAX hp for a warrior at 60 (and that includes 50 HP food ... and ALL HP increasing AA abilities) unbuffed.  I don't believe there is a combination of equip which yields more HP. <br>
<br>
As far as I know the absolute peak of buffed HP with currently known equip is 8118.  Subtract *cough* additional HP buff *cough* from that and you still don't break 7800.<br>
<br>
But this isn't to say that there aren't a lot of tricks to raising HP which I don't know of... also - there have been characters recreated by a GM with HP errors well in excess of what they *should* have.<br>
